Author: Marios Trivyzas <matriv@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 26 19:30:50 2025 +0300

    Fix partition by cols not in group by
    
    The symbols in `partition by` clause of a window function must also
    appear in the `group by` clause of the query, (matching psql behavior).
    Previously, this validation was not applied, therefore a confusing
    message was thrown later on from the planner, e.g.:
    ```
    SELECT sum(x) over(partition by x, y)
    FROM unnest([1], [6]) as t (x, y)
    GROUP BY x
    ```
    thew:
    ```
    UnsupportedFeatureException[Can't handle Symbol [SimpleReference: y]]
    ```
    
    Fixes: #18283
    (cherry picked from commit 422c9d48ae8aee46e0e7550e26d8d326cfa6468d)
    
    # Conflicts:
    #       docs/appendices/release-notes/6.0.1.rst

